post_text: Since Peter Walsh opened Coogan's NYC in 1985, it embodied the best of New York: diverse, welcoming and friendly. It was unlike any other place. Regulars and newcomers agreed: if you wanted to get away from the world, you’d go there. If you wanted to confront the world, you’d go there, too. It was the beating heart of Washington Heights until it closed its doors for the last time in April. Like Coogan’s, 45% of small businesses you love may not survive in the next 3 months without your help. If you need help or can offer it, visit fb.com/supportsmallbusiness

post_text:
Juneteenth commemorates the day in 1865 when the last remaining enslaved people in Galveston, Texas finally learned of their freedom, established by the Emancipation Proclamation over two years before.

We’re honoring its importance by using it as an opportunity to listen and engage in conversation with inspiring leaders in the Black Community like Susan Taylor, Sybrina Fulton and Dr. Eric Michael Dyson. We are grateful for the chance to hear their stories, experiences and the significance this day has for them.

Visit our Lift Black Voices hub on Facebook App and the Instagram Act for Racial Justice Guide to find ways to learn more and participate.

post_text:
We recognize June 19, 1865 as the final day of slavery in the United States. Known as Juneteenth, it commemorates the moment the last remaining enslaved people in Texas learned of their freedom, established by the Emancipation Proclamation two years before.

To honor this day, we’re taking time to become better listeners and greater-informed individuals, so we’re more equipped to take action. This won’t be a conversation reserved for one day, it’s one we’ll continue having until racial injustice is no longer a reality.

Join us, as we work to elevate and amplify underrepresented voices in society. Visit our Lift Black Voices hub on Facebook App and the Instagram Act for Racial Justice Guide to find ways to learn more and participate.

www.facebook.com/liftblackvoices

During this global health challenge, we know there are many questions about where to find accurate information, how to stay connected, and how Facebook is responding. Our focus is on keeping people informed about the coronavirus (COVID-19). We’re sharing a few resources below that will be continually updated.

How can I help?

The World Health Organization has launched the COVID-19 Solidarity Response Fundraiser. Facebook is matching up to $10 million in donations and 100% of funds will directly support the work to prevent, detect and respond to the outbreak around the world: https://www.facebook.com/donate/1564752357011737/10163057684300177/

How is Facebook responding?

Stay up to date on our efforts to respond to the outbreak here: https://about.fb.com/news/2020/03/coronavirus/
